        "goseg/handler/system/support.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`SupportHandlerWithRuntime` decodes JSON (`decodeSupportRequest`), prepares filesystem artifacts, captures optional CPU profile, creates zip output, sends HTTP report, and publishes system transitions.",
        "Failure/success outcomes are handled inline via local state (`supportHandlerOutcome`) and in-function publish hooks, instead of through a dedicated application service boundary."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split this handler into separate layers: request adapter, support artifact service, submission client, and transition publisher; make each component independently testable and composable.",
