    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-02",
      "summary": "Upload pipeline couples multipart transport mechanics with imported-pier domain orchestration and deployment side effects.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "The `importUploadPipeline` type and `run()` method own both transport/session state concerns and post-upload side effects.",
        "Completion step `setUploadFinalizationState` calls `finalizeUploadOnCompletion`, which directly combines chunks and invokes `configureUploadedPier` (which triggers `runImportedPierWorkflowFn` + `runImportedPierPostImportFn`).",
        "This makes lower-level upload handling responsible for deployment decisions and post-processing cleanup behavior."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce an explicit `UploadImportCoordinator` that emits a validated import command and delegates orchestration of imported-pier workflows to a separate ship-import service.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "workflow-policy-leak"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-03",
      "summary": "Broadcast collector function acts as a broad composition hub instead of a narrow projection builder.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`collectUrbitViewInputs` loads urbit config per ship, queries orchestration/container state, consults startram readiness, and builds remote/local UI payload fields in one step.",
        "`ConstructPierInfo` chains `runtimeSnapshotForPiers`, `collectUrbitViewInputs`, and mapper assembly with broad module touchpoints (`config`, `orchestration`, `startram`, `system`, `click`)."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split collector responsibilities into data fetchers (snapshot providers per domain) and a thin composer that only maps domain DTOs into broadcast view models; cache expensive dependencies where applicable.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-04",
      "summary": "Docker lifecycle recovery policy is hard-coded in event flow code, increasing coupling and reducing policy reuse.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/routines/docker.go",
        "goseg/handler/system/recovery.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`dockerStopTransition` enforces restart decisions directly (`startContainerFn`) when desired state is not stopped.",
        "`dockerDieAfterTransition` conditionally schedules background restarts with fixed `2 * time.Second` delay in `scheduleShipRestart`.",
        "`check502Loop` contains fixed polling/retry timing (`180s`, `120s`) and direct recovery delegation, duplicating recovery cadence with other restart paths."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Externalize restart/recovery policy into a typed policy provider (durations, strike thresholds, fallback actions) and inject it into the transition workflow so behavior can be reasoned about and centrally tuned.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "workflow-policy-leak"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Workflow and policy behavior is implemented at handler/runtime edges instead of explicit orchestration/services.",
      "Boundary drift: transport-heavy modules invoke domain lifecycle operations directly, producing coupled responsibilities and hard-coded behavior."
    ],
